headlines.description: — With Patrick Beverley taking the lead in his first season with the team, the Minnesota Timberwolves are trying to prove they’re no longer a pushover.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Edwards star, Wolves beat Giannis-less Bucks 138-119

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 23 points, P.J. Washington added a season-high 21 and the Charlotte Hornets routed the road-weary Dallas Mavericks 129-108 on Saturday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets rout road-weary Mavs 129-108 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — All-Star point guard Darius Garland had 24 points and 12 assists, Evan Mobley had his NBA rookie-high 20th double-double and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Detroit Pistons 113-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 24 points, Cavaliers beat Pistons 113-109

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — LeBron James passed Karl Malone on the career scoring list, leaving only Kareem Abdul-Jabbar still to catch.
headlines.shortLinkText: James passes Malone, but Lakers blow lead in loss to Wizards
